file.title: Compare

p.text: command compares the text and if they are equal returns "0". If not equal, then when the first text on the alphabet above the second, then the command will be equal to -1. If the second text in alphabetical order above the first, then the command returns "1". Thus using this command can, for example, to organize a sort text alphabetically.
